South African musicians who were stranded in Turkey arrived back in the country on Friday night. JOHANNESBURG - Twenty-nine South African musicians who were stranded in Turkey are finally home. They were meant to return when flights were grounded due to the coronavirus outbreak. The group arrived on a Turkish Airways flight on Friday night. READ: Government-led COVID-19 repatriation process criticised Government coordinated their repatriation and placed the group in mandatory quarantine. "As government, we are honoured to have played a role in showing care to our own," Dirco said in a statement. "We are happy that our young practitioners will be back on home soil and soon reunited with their families.”